text.tspan: The economic complexity rankings rank countries from the most economically complex with a rank of 1 (exporting a
diverse range of goods that are not very ubiquitous) to the least economically complex (exporting a narrow variety of
goods that can be commonly produced).
Source: ECI - Observatory of Economic Complexity (OEC) (2016) and the Atlas of Economic Complexity (2016)
